The paper discusses progress in domain-independent planning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It specifically focuses on heuristic functions and their effectiveness in solving planning problems, which falls under planning and scheduling (cs.PL). The paper also discusses topology and search algorithms, which are topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the theoretical investigation and analysis of problem structure and search performance, which falls under software engineering (cs.SE).
